The paper deals with the problem of maximizing non-negative monotone submodular functions under certain constraints, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The problem is related to optimization, algorithms, and data structures, which are all covered by the arXiv sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which are often studied in the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of evaluation oracles and the design of polynomial-time algorithms suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category cs.IT (Information Theory). The problem of maximizing submodular functions is also related to combinatorial optimization, which is covered by the sub-category cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper's focus on monotone submodular functions and its use of approximation algorithms suggest that it may be relevant to the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
